---

<BaseLayout title="CV" description="Darryl Cauldwell - Customer Success Architect with 30+ years in enterprise IT, cloud infrastructure, and virtualization">
  <!-- Schema.org structured data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(jsonLd)} />

  <div class="max-w-[var(--max-width)] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 cv-container">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Header with print button -->
      <header class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b-2 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4" style={`border-color: ${meAccentColor};`}>
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--color-heading)]">Darryl Cauldwell</h1>
          <p class="text-xl font-medium mt-1" style={`color: ${meAccentColor};`}>Customer Success Architect</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-2">
            <a href="mailto:darryl.cauldwell@gmail.com" class="hover:text-[var(--color-accent)]">darryl.cauldwell@gmail.com</a>
            <span class="mx-2">‚Ä¢</span>
            <a href="https://blog.dreamfold.dev" class="hover:text-[var(--color-accent)]">blog.dreamfold.dev</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <button
          onclick="window.print()"
          class="print-hide self-start sm:self-auto px-4 py-2 text-white rounded-lg transition-colors flex items-center gap-2"
          style={`background-color: ${meAccentColor};`}
        >
          <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 17h2a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v4a2 2 0 002 2h2m2 4h6a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v4a2 2 0 002 2zm8-12V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H9a2 2 0 00-2 2v4h10z" />
          </svg>
          <span>Print / PDF</span>
        </button>
      </header>

      <!-- Summary -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <p class="text-[var(--color-text)] text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Enterprise architect with <strong>30+ years</strong> progressing from hands-on engineering through automation, DevOps, and product management to delivering cloud infrastructure solutions across
          <strong>VMware</strong>, <strong>Kubernetes</strong>, and <strong>public cloud</strong> platforms.
          A recurring theme throughout my career has been designing solutions, proving them in production, and then scaling or replicating them across regions and organisations.
          I provide architectural guidance for customers developing highly automated, secure, available, resilient, and multi-cloud architectural designs.
          The designs typically need to seamlessly integrate with very complex estates which requires focussed problem-solving and analytical skills.
          Recognised with <strong>12 industry awards</strong> for technical excellence and innovation.
          Passionate about sustainability, community contribution, and enabling customer success.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Key Metrics -->
      <section class="mb-8 print-hide">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-[var(--color-translucent)] rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-accent)]">30+</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Years Experience</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-[var(--color-translucent)] rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-accent)]">12</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Industry Awards</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-[var(--color-translucent)] rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-accent)]">50+</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Certifications</div>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 bg-[var(--color-translucent)] rounded-lg">
            <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-accent)]">11+</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Years vExpert</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Experience Timeline -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="section-title">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 13.255A23.931 23.931 0 0112 15c-3.183 0-6.22-.62-9-1.745M16 6V4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v2m4 6h.01M5 20h14a2 2 0 002-2V8a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2z" />
          </svg>
          Professional Experience
        </h2>

        <div class="experience-list">
          <!-- VMware -->
          <div class="company-card current">
            <details open>
              <summary class="company-header">
                <div class="company-info">
                  <div class="company-title-row">
                    <h3>VMware</h3>
                    <span class="company-date">2019 - Present</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="company-role">Customer Success Architect</p>
                  <p class="company-summary">Providing architectural guidance for multi-cloud designs, OCTO Ambassador for edge/sustainability innovation</p>
                  <div class="company-badges">
                    <span class="badge">3 Awards</span>
                    <span class="badge">3 Roles</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <svg class="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="company-roles">
                <details class="role-accordion" open>
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Customer Success Architect - Success 360</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Sep 2020 - Present</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Provide architectural guidance for customers developing highly automated, secure, available, resilient, and multi-cloud architectural designs. Formulate architectural roadmaps harmonising customer and product roadmaps. Help customers develop project plans mapping their journey from current to desired future state, guiding them through business process transformation to achieve outcomes. Managed customer health scoring, tracking adoption, satisfaction, and risk indicators. Delivered executive business reviews presenting roadmaps, value realisation, and recommendations to C-level stakeholders. Drove adoption acceleration by identifying underutilised licenses and feature consumption gaps. Proactive risk mitigation covering technical debt, upgrade gaps, and end-of-life exposure. Cross-portfolio architecture spanning VCF, NSX, Tanzu, and Aria across hybrid and multi-cloud environments including VMware on AWS, Azure VMware Solution, and Google Cloud VMware Engine. Delivered architecture design workshops, hands-on labs, and knowledge transfer. Defined measurable success plans and tracked progress against outcomes. Bridged customer escalations to engineering and product teams, and contributed patterns and lessons learned across the CSA community of practice.</p>
                    <div class="role-achievements">
                      <span>üèÜ 'Raising the Bar' Award FY21</span>
                      <span>üèÜ 'Execution' Award FY23 Q1</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">OCTO Ambassador</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Feb 2021 - Present</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Conduit between customers and R&D teams for innovation awareness and design partnerships. Focus on edge computing, IT/OT convergence, sustainability and carbon reduction. Delivered technology previews of pre-release VMware technologies and facilitated innovation workshops exploring how emerging tech solves customer challenges. Paired customers with R&D in design partnerships for early product feedback, and advocated internally to influence product roadmaps with customer requirements. Built proof of concepts for emerging use cases including edge computing and AI/ML at the edge. Thought leadership through conference talks, blog posts, and whitepapers. Cross-functional collaboration across business units including Tanzu, NSX, VCF, and Aria. Sustainability work included carbon footprint measurement and power-aware workload placement, with IT/OT convergence bridging traditional IT with operational technology in manufacturing and utilities. Active engagement with industry standards bodies and sustainability networks.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Embedded Architect - Advanced Customer Engagement</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Jul 2019 - Sep 2020</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Embedded architect within strategic alliance partner's hybrid cloud teams. As a customer success architect, enabled strategic alliance partners to develop service products on top of VMware Cloud Foundation. Dual focus - helping partners create standardised product offerings and tailoring solutions for specific large customer opportunities. On-point for architectural aspects of the full VMware portfolio including consultancy, enablement, design partnerships, and executive briefings.</p>
                    <div class="role-achievements">
                      <span>üèÜ ACE 'Leadership' Award FY20</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <!-- DXC Technology -->
          <div class="company-card">
            <details>
              <summary class="company-header">
                <div class="company-info">
                  <div class="company-title-row">
                    <h3>DXC Technology</h3>
                    <span class="company-date">2016 - 2019</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="company-role">Principal Architect</p>
                  <p class="company-summary">Led design of standardised IaaS private cloud with self-service PaaS catalogue for defence, government, and healthcare</p>
                  <div class="company-badges">
                    <span class="badge">3 Roles</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <svg class="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="company-roles">
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Managed Services for VMware Private Cloud</span>
                    <span class="role-date">May 2017 - Jul 2019</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Led design and engineering team developing standardised IaaS private cloud, building on the Modern Platform foundational architecture I designed earlier. Comprehensive self-service PaaS catalogue delivering servers, databases, middleware, security, backup, DR, and NFV for defence, government, financial, and healthcare customers. Another product-on-a-product role - the key differentiator over the Managed Mid-range offering was self-service consumption with full automation and orchestration, giving customers direct control over provisioning without raising tickets.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Managed Mid-range on VMware</span>
                    <span class="role-date">May 2017 - Jul 2019</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Technical design and engineering lead for global Managed Mid-range offering. Developed highly standardised hosting platform enabling streamlined day-two operational support with flexibility for workload customisation. Built on the Modern Platform foundational building blocks, turning platform capabilities into consumable services integrated with ITSM. Essentially productising the standardised infrastructure into a managed mid-range offering with service catalogue, operational workflows, and day-two support models.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Modern Platform Initiative</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Dec 2016 - Jul 2019</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Technical lead industrialising VMware platform delivery. My first role as product manager rather than architect, introducing new skills in stakeholder management, backlog prioritisation, and agile sprints. The team adapted Agile to Scaled Agile (SAFe) for architecture and product management. Technically complex due to the scale of deployments - modular designs ensured consistent factory builds across Dell, Hitachi, and HPE hardware, with delivery workflows integrating all data centre systems.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <!-- Atos -->
          <div class="company-card">
            <details>
              <summary class="company-header">
                <div class="company-info">
                  <div class="company-title-row">
                    <h3>Atos</h3>
                    <span class="company-date">2015 - 2016</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="company-role">Principal Architect</p>
                  <p class="company-summary">Transitioned engineering to iterative DevOps, introduced Ansible automation, architected AWS managed cloud</p>
                  <div class="company-badges">
                    <span class="badge">3 Roles</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <svg class="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="company-roles">
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Cloud DevOps</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Dec 2015 - Dec 2016</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Transitioned Global Cloud Engineering from monolithic to iterative delivery. Introduced Ansible automation for desired-state infrastructure configuration, reducing incidents and improving customer satisfaction. Drove the Ansible adoption strategy across Global Cloud Engineering, evangelising automation to replace ad-hoc scripting with standardised playbook development. Infrastructure code moved into Atlassian source control with code review workflows, establishing repeatable and auditable delivery practices.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Managed Public Cloud (AWS)</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Sep 2016 - Dec 2016</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Architected and automated AWS-based Managed Public Cloud offering with centralised management, billing, monitoring, and security via ServiceNow. Primarily focused on Ansible automation for infrastructure provisioning and CloudFormation templates for repeatable deployments. Extensive IAM design for cross-VPC and cross-account working with federated identity. Built cost reporting for showback and chargeback to give customers billing transparency. Integrated the platform with ServiceNow for ITSM workflows and managed customer onboarding including account provisioning, baseline security, and connectivity setup.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Centralised Control Hub (NSX)</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Dec 2015 - Sep 2016</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Technical lead for site-resilient NSX solution connecting 31 remote sites via Edge Services Gateway VPN tunnels with micro-segmentation firewall rules. Designed the NSX architecture including controller cluster sizing, transport zones, and VXLAN configuration, integrated with the vSphere platform including host preparation and VTEP configuration. The solution brought together two Atos products - DDC and Enterprise Private Cloud - into a unified, site-resilient network architecture.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>

          <!-- CSC -->
          <div class="company-card">
            <details>
              <summary class="company-header">
                <div class="company-info">
                  <div class="company-title-row">
                    <h3>Computer Sciences Corporation (CSC)</h3>
                    <span class="company-date">2004 - 2015</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="company-role">Architect / Platform Systems Engineer</p>
                  <p class="company-summary">11 years delivering cloud, DevOps, and automation solutions for healthcare, government, and enterprise</p>
                  <div class="company-badges">
                    <span class="badge">4 Awards</span>
                    <span class="badge">13 Roles</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <svg class="chevron" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="company-roles">
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">BizCloud Hyper-Converged</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Mar 2014 - Dec 2015</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Designed and automated private cloud infrastructure using hyper-converged VMware SDDC. Showcased how automation enables rapid, consistent provisioning - reducing time to production and freeing teams from manual infrastructure work. This was essentially building a VMware SDDC stack - the pattern that later became VCF - but before VCF existed. Ansible automation handled the full SDDC provisioning - we wrote and published Ansible modules for ESXi host and vSAN management in vCenter. The arrival of VMware NSX for vSphere significantly changed the SDN automation landscape, requiring rework of the network provisioning layer. Jenkins CI pipelines provided the consumption layer for self-service delivery of servers, applications, SDN, distributed firewall, and NFV.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - DevOps Transformation</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Apr 2013 - Mar 2014</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Transformed development workflow from static releases to continuous delivery using Service Mesh Agility Platform and Puppet. Declarative infrastructure as code replaced manual processes - delivering consistency, improved availability, lower operational costs, and faster time to value. Introduced Puppet with Razor for bare-metal provisioning and Ansible engine for desired-state configuration management. Helped write the Service Mesh Agility Platform plugin for NSX-MH, delivering layer 2 network provisioning, layer 3 routing configuration, and NSX load balancers for network function virtualisation (NFV).</p>
                    <div class="role-achievements">
                      <span>üèÜ CSC Global Award for Technical Excellence 2015</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - Storage Consolidation</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Dec 2012 - Apr 2013</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Multi-petabyte storage with 99.99% availability - a significant engineering challenge. Evaluated EMC VMAX and Hitachi VSP, led consolidation to unified Hitachi VSP. Hard work paid off - major cost savings, performance improvements, virtualised LUNs enabling data mobility, and improved data replication. As architect I oversaw the full delivery lifecycle. Migration planning sequenced workload moves with minimal downtime windows, with risk management and rollback plans for each wave. Redesigned host presentation including fibre channel zoning, multipathing policies, and HBA firmware. Implemented SRDF for disaster recovery replication on the new platform. Managed decommissioning of legacy EMC arrays and provided stakeholder reporting to programme board tracking progress and cost savings.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">CSC Internal - Global Systems Management</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Jan 2012 - Nov 2012</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Designed, engineered, and delivered a vSphere hosting platform for global systems management tooling. The monitoring platform required a higher SLA than the services it monitored to ensure contractual reporting obligations were met. Designed with dedicated infrastructure isolated from customer workloads to avoid shared-fate failures, strict high availability with vSphere HA admission control policies, and robust backup and DR to protect historical monitoring data as contractual evidence.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - Stateless Application Deployment</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Aug 2011 - Dec 2011</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Building on decomposing monolithic applications into delivery units, this role focused on increasing velocity from code to production. Developed stateless application deployment using VHD detachment/attachment with PowerShell, NetApp snapshots, and VMware. Not a CI pipeline yet, but the forerunner to streamlined delivery with governance and control. Worked very closely with the application software architecture team as the infrastructure architect, designing a joined-up end-to-end solution that coupled best-of-breed infrastructure technology with an innovative approach to software delivery. Breaking the monolith into independently deployable units was ahead of its time - a pattern that has since become mainstream with microservices architecture.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - vCloud Director IaaS</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Oct 2011</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Technical lead for vCloud Director self-service IaaS on VCE vBlock for hospital trust. Introducing multi-tenancy enabled better use of assets through increased resource sharing with guarantees - applications functioned as required. Built on VCE vBlock converged infrastructure - Cisco UCS blades, EMC storage, and Cisco Nexus networking. Configured vCloud Director with organisations, virtual datacentres, catalogs, and vApp templates. Network pools provided tenant isolation, with vShield Edge delivering NAT, firewall, DHCP, and VPN per tenant. Resource allocation models and vCenter Chargeback Manager enabled cost transparency. Curated VM catalogs gave hospital trust teams self-service provisioning without raising tickets. Designed to meet NHS IG Toolkit compliance and data separation requirements for patient data, with operational handover and training for the new self-service model.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">CSC Internal - Nordics vCloud Director</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Apr 2011 - Aug 2011</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Designed and led vCloud Director self-service IaaS implementation for Nordics region, collaborating with local delivery engineers. Multi-tenancy enabled better asset utilisation through resource sharing with guarantees, ensuring applications performed as required. Building on the proven vCloud Director architecture from the healthcare project, adapted the design for Nordic regional requirements. Worked onsite with local delivery engineers, addressing data sovereignty considerations across Nordic countries. Created documentation and knowledge transfer to enable local teams to own and operate the platform independently - proving the architecture was repeatable across regions.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - VMware Hosting Redesign</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Aug 2009 - Dec 2011</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Hardware technology refresh - led rearchitecting the VMware hosting solution for more robust scale and DR capability. Innovative NetApp partnership enabled transglobal data replication. Complemented by decomposing a monolithic application into smaller, independently shippable delivery units. Central to this was migrating storage to NetApp across the UK and Chennai sites, with SnapMirror replication enabling transglobal data mobility. NetApp snapshots provided disaster recovery capability and enabled reporting data to be split from OLTP databases - removing analytical workloads from production. The database tier ran on massive HPE Itanium SuperDome IA64 systems, making certification and validation particularly complex. Upgraded through vSphere 4.x to 5.0, implementing HA and DRS clustering for availability and load balancing. VMware SRM automated DR failover between sites. NetApp ONTAP configuration included deduplication, thin provisioning, and FlexClone for dev/test copies. VMware Update Manager handled ESXi patching at scale. Performance baselining validated the redesign with before/after metrics, and capacity planning drove consolidation ratios and VM right-sizing. N+1 resilience design ensured host and chassis failures wouldn't impact patient-facing systems. Application dependency mapping, change management for zero-downtime migration of production healthcare workloads, and vendor coordination across NetApp, HPE, and VMware.</p>
                    <div class="role-achievements">
                      <span>üèÜ NetApp EMEA Innovation Award 2011</span>
                      <span>üèÜ CSC Global Presidents Award 2011</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">Identity and Passport Services</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Jun 2009 - Aug 2009</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Architect for UK Government Identity and Passport Services. Security, identity access management, and regulatory compliance were paramount. Gathered requirements, designed and implemented a VMware virtual hosting solution with extensive automation enabling several hundred developers and testers to rapidly spin up environments. Platform was vSphere 4.0, designed to meet government IL3/IL4 security accreditation with CESG guidance. Strict network segregation with VLAN isolation, separate Active Directory forests for security boundaries, and hardened builds to government security baselines. Role-based access control in vCenter with audit logging, and encryption for data at rest and in transit to protect sensitive personal data. Produced RMADS security documentation for accreditation.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - Developer Cloud</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Jun 2008 - Jun 2009</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Consistency was the goal - dev and test environments that matched production to reduce issues when shipping code. Created automation spanning infrastructure configuration, application deployment, configuration, and lifecycle management through Altiris. This was my first role as VMware architect - designed the full stack including HPE blade chassis and storage array to build a VI3 hosting platform for the development and test environments. Managed the platform through VirtualCenter, designed Fibre Channel SAN with VMFS datastores and multipathing, and implemented VMware Consolidated Backup (VCB). Capacity management ensured the platform was right-sized as demand grew. Based in Chennai where I recruited and trained the local engineering and operations teams, which grew to 114 engineers and managers at peak. In Chennai, created runbooks and operational documentation for knowledge transfer, completed ITIL service transition from project to BAU operations, and established monitoring via HP Operations Manager.</p>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK Border Agency (Belgrade)</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Jun 2007</span>
                  </summary>
                  <div class="role-content">
                    <p>Deployed nationally sensitive IT infrastructure at the VFS Global Visa Application Centre in Belgrade - the primary location for UK visa applications in Serbia, handling document scanning and biometric data collection. VACs were located on industrial estates to protect embassies, so the system required robust and reliable communications back to embassy systems over distance.</p>
                    <div class="role-achievements">
                      <span>üèÜ MCA International Award 2007</span>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </details>
                <details class="role-accordion">
                  <summary class="role-header">
                    <span class="role-title">UK&I Healthcare - Enterprise Automation</span>
                    <span class="role-date">Sep 2004 - Jun 2008</span>
